###Finding $BC$

In a $45\degree$-$45\degree$-$90\degree$ triangle, the hypotenuse is longer than a leg by a factor of $\sqrt2$. Let's use this ratio and the fact that $AB=12$ to solve for the leg length $BC$, which is $x$.

$\begin{align}
(\text{leg length}) \cdot \sqrt2 &= \text{hypotenuse length}
\\\\
x \cdot \sqrt2 &= 12
\\\\
x &= \dfrac{12}{\sqrt2} 
\\\\
x &= \dfrac{12}{\sqrt2} \cdot \dfrac{\sqrt2}{\sqrt2}
\\\\
x &= \dfrac{12\sqrt2}{2}
\\\\
x &= 6\sqrt2
\end{align}$

